<a href=http://www.phank.com>Phank</a>, Druzzil Ro<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/uepiphanyeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Epiphany EQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Druzzil Ro Member</span><br>  Posts: 119<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(2/17/02 10:25:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/fdruzzilro86846frm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1089.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.phank.com/avitars/epiphanysmall.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reserving CoM Reavers?  Discuss</span><hr size=1> Well here's your vote thread right here Aana.<br>
<br>
As for what I think, I'm not sure.  It's not like you need a guild effort just to zone into CoM like you do with Hate.  They respawn fast so you wouldn't have to wait 8 hours after somebody else cleared em.  But they are important for the growth of low level guilds, and they are heavily camped.<br>
<br>
I am frustrated by my inability to find them uncamped, and that leads me to want to reserve them.  However I have to recognize that The Ghoul Lord in LGuk is just as heavily camped (or more so), and yet nobody has suggested reserving him.<br>
<br>
As I ramble along, I find myself thinking that though I might wish to reserve the suckers for my own personal needs, it would be inappropriate to do so.<br>
<br>
If I expect you to respect my Reaver reservation, I'm going to have to respect your VL ledge reservation.  I just can't see any way around that.  Since I would really rather not have arguments over who stomped who's reservation of the VL ledge, I am forced to vote &quot;nay&quot; on the reavers as well.<br>
<br>
So for now, I'll be sure not to bother heading to CoM when I've noticed someone's posted &quot;intentions&quot; to be there - that would be a waste of my time.  But if I hadn't noticed the reservation and I had arrived at the camp first, I would be put-out if they were to ask me to leave.<br>
<br>
As with Aanadien, if a reasonable majority does want to start reserving the Reavers, I will absolutely go along with it.<br>
<br>
