<br>
You refuse to acknowledge that there's even a question as to which reservations the DRo board should cover--if people post it, that's valid, the system can be expanded to cover literally ANYTHING people want to reserve, and so it's simply a matter of who respects the system (and therefore must commit to respecting any reservation anyone posts) and who doesn't (and therefore deserves to have none of their reservations respected.)<br>
<br>
If you start from the assumption that any posted reservation is valid, then your position makes sense.<br>
<br>
But why do that?<br>
<br>
The whole question in this thread is SHOULD CoM be reservable?  You make a convincing case that IF the answer is yes, everyone should honor the reservation.  What if the answer is no?<br>
<br>
I think the answer should definitely be &quot;No.&quot;  I think everyone should carefully honor any valid reservation, and we should very very carefully limit the things that can be reserved.<br>
<br>
The alternative is to hold DRo board guilds to an unreasonably high standard, one they won't even WANT to live up to because it stands in direct conflict with years of EQ tradition, and they'll eventually just bail on it. <p>----------------------------------------<BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=89094>Jumpp Jivenwail</a>, 60 Rogue<BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=97652>Aanadien Jones</a>, 60 Enchanter<BR>
<a href=http://www.phank.com>Phank</a>, Druzzil Ro<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/ugrazel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grazel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Valiant Elite IGB Rep</span><br>  Posts: 213<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(2/18/02 3:23:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/fdruzzilro86846frm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1089.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reserving CoM Reavers?  Discuss</span><hr size=1> IMO:<br>
<br>
Reservation: A posting for a mob/zone/area from a specific list. (The list would have highly contested mobs/areas that most everyone here agrees should be reservable.)<br>
<br>
Intentions: A request for a mob/zone/location that isn't on the list. If someone is there when you arrive, you can ask them (politely) to leave or share, but don't expect them to.<br>
<br>
<br>
The key is having a list.<br>
