<br>
It has nothing to do with being inconsiderate, or selfish.<br>
<br>
Let's just say a group of IG decides that we want to kill reavers cause someone, I dunno who, needs their epic.  We get to CoM.  No one is there.  So we go and kill some reavers.  Whee.  If someone is there and says 'we are killing the reavers' I cannot see us caring one way or the other, and we will head to Sebilis or something to kill the King or Emperor or whatnot.  But what we won't do, just because it doesn't occur to us, really, is to check a reservation for CoM.  And if someone shows up 10 minutes after we clear them, well, just wait a little bit, won't be long.<br>
<br>
This is different from, well, Hate or Fear.  We do look for reservations there, or see if someone is there, because it is a lot bigger deal to everyone than CoM.  8 hours makes a huge difference.  Needing a raid sized force makes a big difference.<br>
<br>
In the thread on the other board you listed IG as scum balls (or something of the sort) apparently merely for showing UP in Kedge.  Once they found out that someone, anyone, was killing Phinny, they left (I wasn't there).  You try to make the point that they left merely because they knew ML was there.  You don't seem to ponder the thought that they didn't look here for a Kedge raid reservation, because why reserve Kedge?  (again, from our perspective).  But they didn't muscle in, they didn't steal Phinny, they didn't, from what you say, berate you or belittle you.  They found someone killing Phinny and left.  Case closed.  Any attempt to make it something sinister really doesn't fly.  All checking for reservations would have done is save themselves the trip, in reality.<br>
<br>
This would be different if you were there, setting up to crush the joint, killing front spawns, etc, and guild X decides to swim past you and bag Phinny, even after you tell them that you are there.  First Come, First Serve is what you were doing.  You were there, you were getting ready to kill.  Free For All is rushing past people who are obviously about to do..whatever...and taking it out from under them.  Even Vindication, in their NToV grabbing (best term I can think of for it), didn't stoop to that level.<br>
<br>
I think you will find that THAT is a relative rarity on the server.  Which is a good thing. <br>
<br>
I also think that more good things happen between guilds, even Uber guild to Uber guild..and Uber guild to NON-Uber guild, than bad.  Way more.  But most of those are small niceties that just never make press.<br>
<br>
But screaming and yelling does.<br>
<br>
Gryfalia <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/utinydru.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TinyDru</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(2/19/02 10:30:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/fdruzzilro86846frm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1089.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reserving CoM Reavers?  Discuss</span><hr size=1> Gryfalia - I understand your point (as I also understand many of the other well-made points here as well).  You bring up the root of my issue though - time.  It IS a big deal to me if someone has just whacked all of the Reavers due to the fact that I have a pretty limited window in which I can play EQ.  Waiting for the respawn (by the way - has anyone confirmed whether this is a 1 hour or a 2 hour spawn?) just makes that window of opportunity all the smaller for me and others like me.  Again - it takes time to gather the people to do something like this - and then making them wait on top of it - you start to lose folks after a while, some have to log, etc.<br>
<br>
With all of that being said - I must also consider that this might be just the way EQ works (and I am not trying to be sarcastic or nasty in any way here) - those with more time will be able to get more done and those with less time will just have to make due.  I can't very well ask another EQ player to forgo something that he/she wants to do just because my time on EQ is limited.<br>
<br>
Hmmm - now I've confused myself (which really isn't that difficult in the first place... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).  On the one hand, I feel that a place like CoM SHOULD be able to be reserved / intentioned due to the fact that it has a fairly rare mob drop required for one of the Epic quests AND that it, for many people, requires a small raid sized group to get it done.  On the other hand, if the timer on the Reavers is indeed only an hour, perhaps that would be short enough to still gather the raid force, but to simply have them take their time getting to the castle (kill more stuff on the way).  This would probably work ok, but if the respawn is two hours, this would get a lot closer to being unworkable.<br>
<br>
In the end, I am still for being able to reserve CoM due to the reasons I mentioned above.  I understand that this does not mean that CoM is MINE MINE ALL MINE for the day - I think that placing an arrival time and a specific mob target helps with this.  I also understand that by placing a reservation on the board that the time slot is not guarunteed due to the fact that there are many people who do not look at this board.  What I AM hoping for is that the large number of people / guilds who DO read this board will respect that time slot and shoot for something else (the same as they are hopefully doing for Hate, Kael, etc.).  Kind of like pushing the time slot odds in the &quot;right&quot; direction.<br>
<br>
It appears to me that CoM (as well as Kedge and some others) have been on the reservation schedule for some time now (although I have not been browsing this board for a very long time, so I may be wrong).  It also appears to me that there is not a big explosion of guilds / people wanting to reserve previously unreserved things.  My guess is that there will remain a fairly static list of areas to be reserved with minor updates and changes as time goes by - it shouldn't be that hard to keep track of.  I don't think that leaving spots like Kedge and CoM on the list will open the flood gates to reserving everything in EQ.<br>
<br>
Whether we consider something reserved or simply a statement of intent, I would like to think that, given enough lead time on the posting, the people / guilds who participate on this board would be curtious enough to respect that posting.<br>
<br>
-Pinelda <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/ukaludramaderlas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaludram Aderlas</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.fortunecity.com/samslade/shadcon/Images/minisc.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Druzzil Ro Member</span><br>  Posts: 415<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(2/19/02 11:29:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/fdruzzilro86846frm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1089.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reserving CoM Reavers?  Discuss</span><hr size=1> Gryfalia, you are correct.  I was in a bad mood and all this FFA garbage and arguing over spawns in getting on my nerves.  IG did nothing wrong imo, and I apologize for my words.  <br>
